    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for high-upside output today, anchored by the elite 83.36 projection for **Kyle Tucker**. Facing Lorenzen, **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and a favorable order placement, making him the premier play. He is joined in the must-start tier by **Andy Pages** (70.02) and **Jacob Wilson** (71.63), the latter of whom exploits a high 6.23 xERA matchup against Schultz. **Miguel Vargas** (66.77) also warrants attention; while he is currently pending a final lineup check, the data rewards him for his high-base projection and the fact that the opposing battery allows an 86% success rate for base stealers\u2014an essential metric given our emphasis on the scarcity of SBs.\n\nStrategic adjustments were required to optimize our roster against today\u2019s slate of left-handed starters. **Gunnar Henderson** remains a start despite a 15% hit to his score due to the platoon disadvantage against Cantillo, as his baseline talent is simply too high to bench. The most difficult decision involved **Nolan Schanuel** (51.94), who narrowly missed the cut behind **Heliot Ramos** and **Josh Lowe**. While **Nolan Schanuel** projects as a stable floor play, the optimizer favored **Josh Lowe** due to his 14% platoon edge, and the overall roster construction prioritized speed-heavy profiles to close the gap in the SB category. \n\nManagement must remain vigilant regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" statuses for **Drake Baldwin**, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Andy Pages**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Josh Lowe**, and **Nolan Schanuel**. Any late-breaking injury news or drastic shifts in batting order could necessitate a pivot toward **Coby Mayo** or **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, both of whom are ready on the bench. While **Marcell Ozuna** carries a modest 52.42 score, he is cleared to start today as wind conditions at the venue provide a necessary +5% lift to his power profile, compensating for the tough matchup against McClanahan.",
